title: Arizona Firm Recalls Chicken Breast Fritters Products Due to Misbranding and an Undeclared Allergen
summary: WASHINGTON, Jan. 23, 2015 Primecut Meats, a Phoenix, Ariz. establishment, is recalling approximately 17,700 pounds of chicken breast fritters products due to misbranding and an undeclared allergen, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
